<subSubSection pageId="39" pageNumber="40" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="39.[151,1437,798,1651]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,1554,1579]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species differs from 
<taxonomicName authority="Evans, 1966" authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1966" box="[649,952,1554,1579]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jocundus">
<emphasis box="[649,789,1554,1579]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">A. jocundus</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation box="[805,952,1554,1579]" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" refId="ref280374" refString="Evans, H. E. (1966) A revision of the genus Anisepyris Kieffer (Hymenoptera. Bethylidae). Studia Entomologica, 9, 1 - 120." type="journal article">Evans, 1966</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
by having the frons without a median impression; the ocelli very small; and the mesopleuron with all foveae closed, whereas 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Evans" authorityYear="1966" box="[1148,1281,1590,1615]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Anisepyris" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="39" pageNumber="40" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="jocundus">
<emphasis box="[1148,1281,1590,1615]" italics="true" pageId="39" pageNumber="40">A. jocundus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has the frons with a median impression; the mesopleuron with the lower foveae closed; and the mesopleural suture opened.
</paragraph>
